==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midwife
<hw>Mid"wife`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Midwives</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>midwif</ets>, fr.
AS. <ets>mid</ets> with (akin to Gr. <?/) + <?/ woman, wife. Properly,
the woman or wife who is attendant upon a woman in childbirth. See
<er>Meta-</er>, and <er>Wife</er>.]</ety> <def>A woman who assists other
women in childbirth; a female practitioner of the obstetric
art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midwife</ent>⟦br⟧

